data.name: label_WADList.Text
data.value:
Map2Curve requires info about texture-widths and -heights. Add any WAD file (WAD3) you are using in your input maps before generating new curves.
If it exists, the WAD-list will be acquired from Map2Curve\WAD\WADList.txt on GUI startup and saved there when changed. For this to work the location of Map2Curve.exe has to be specified in the Settings-tab.

data.name: label8.Text
data.value: Sometimes it might be necessary for Map2Curve to triangulate the brushes of a curve. Situations that require triangulation are height+ramp, "snap to grid" and sheared texture mapping. For this to work efficiently on complex objects like cylinders as well, they should be setup similar to figure 2 or 3.

data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
Object made from one brush only.
Recommended when triangulation isn't needed at all.
When triangulation is necessary, complex brushes like this will be turned into many spike brushes (very inefficient, not recommended).

data.name: label11.Text
data.value:
First and last corner have to share the same location to form a loop!
Corners can have different z-coordinates.
When using this method it is not possible to add new corners inside of a finished path, only at its end! Use the path-tool of your favorite editor to be more flexible. Export the file to map-format to turn it into path_corner entities. Example shows Simple Path Extrusion.

data.name: label25.Text
data.value:
2) Use the following settings:
[Tab: General] Curve Framework Type: Circle Flatten Pi Circle Framework: Yes
[Tab: Detail Objects] Carve Detail Objects: Yes
If you want to quickly put all loose entities into one detail-group, use this as well:
[Tab: Detail Objects] Put all ungrouped..into one Detail Object: Yes

data.name: label22.Text
data.value:
3) Create a info_detailgroup point-entity (included in Map2Curve.fgd).
Assign the same group-name to it ("lamp").
Here you can control your detail-object individually. These settings will overwrite any settings in tab "Detail Objects".

data.name: label12.Text
data.value:
Detail objects are brush- and/or point entities that are not turned into curve brushes, but copied in one piece and pasted along the curve (once per section).
Yaw, pitch and location can be controlled and randomized.
Usually this would be used for detailing curves with lamps or wall-mounted objects.
